HEADWORD: Melodiograph
<hw>Me*lo"di*o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Melody</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>A contrivance
for preserving a record of music, by recording the action of the keys of
a musical instrument when played upon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melodious</ent>⟦br⟧
